President Obama spoke with Iraqi Prime Minister Haider al-Abadi to discuss the situation in Iraq and the progress of Iraqi Security Forces in their efforts to counter ISIL. The President commended Prime Minister al-Abadi for his inclusive governance and efforts to unite Iraqis against ISIL. He also congratulated him on the recent oil revenue-sharing arrangement with the Kurdistan Regional Government. The President reaffirmed his commitment to supporting the Iraqi Security Forces through training, providing weapons and equipment, and conducting airstrikes. He also expressed support for the integration of Sunni tribal fighters into Iraq's security institutions.